      public Vector​(double x, double y, double z)
      Creates a Vector object with the given dimensions.

      x - Dimension in x.
      y - Dimension in y.
      z - Dimension in z.

    • Vector

      public Vector​(Point3D P)
      Creates a Vector object using the given Point. The starting point of the Vector is the origin of the 3D space, and the endpoint is the position of the Point.
      Parameters:
      P - The endpoint of the desired vector.

    • Vector

      public Vector​(Point3D start, Point3D end)
      Creates a Vector object using two Point objects as the starting and ending positions. The resulting vector will always point TOWARDS the endpoint.
      Parameters:
      start - The origin of the vector.
      end - The endpoint of the vector.

  • Method Details

    • reflected

      public static Vector reflected​(Vector incidence, Vector normal)
      Reflects the given incidence vector about the given normal vector.
      Parameters:
      incidence - The incoming Vector to be reflected.
      normal - The Vector perpendicular to a surface, that the incidence Vector will reflect across.
      Returns:
      Normalized Vector representing the result of the reflection.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if either of the incidence or normal vectors have a magnitude of zero.
      See Also:
      normalize()

    • randomHemi

      public static Vector randomHemi​(Vector VZ)
      Generates a random Vector that is within the hemisphere surrounding the given Vector. Specifically, the new Vector will be within 90 degrees of the given Vector, in a random direction.
      Parameters:
      VZ - The Vector from which the hemisphere will be constructed.
      Returns:
      A random Vector within the constructed hemisphere.

    • normalize

      public void normalize()
      Updates the current Vector to have a magnitude of 1, while maintaining its original direction. If the magnitude of the current Vector is zero, nothing will change.
      See Also:
      getMagnitude()

      public Vector mult​(double n)

      public Vector crossProd​(Vector V)

      Returns:
      New Vector holding the result of the operation.

    • parseVector

      public static Vector parseVector​(java.lang.String[] S)
      Returns a Vector with the dimensions specified in the String[] argument.
      Parameters:
      S - String[] array to be parsed.
      Returns:
      Vector with (x, y, z) dimensions extracted from the given String[].
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given String[] is not of length 3.

    • toString

      public java.lang.String toString()
      Returns a String representation of the current Vector. This representation consists of the x, y and z dimensions of the Vector separated by spaces.
      Overrides:
      toString in class java.lang.Object
      Returns:
